    <stitle>FRONT NON-DRIVE STEERING AXLE: ROCKWELL - DISASSEMBLE - BUSHINGS FROM THE KNUCKLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>BUSHINGS FROM THE KNUCKLE</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Remove and discard the seal in front of the bushing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200512">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200512" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200512" filename="../figg02/G0200512.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Remove Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Nylon Bushings</title>
            <para>Remove the top and the bottom bushing from the knuckle bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200513">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200513" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200513" filename="../figg02/G0200513.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Remove Bushing</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bronze and Easy Steer Bushings</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>On FF-, FG- and FL-Series axles, the bushings can be removed with KING PIN BUSHING SERVICE
                        SET. Refer to the
                        <hotlnk document="s02005r_33.xml" xrefid="hl0200505">SPECIAL TOOLS</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put the knuckle on a press. Use a press with a 5 ton capacity. Make sure the knuckle
                    does not move when the bushings are removed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tool in the top bushing. Press the top bushing from the knuckle bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200514">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200514" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200514" filename="../figg02/G0200514.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Top and Bottom Bushing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tool in the bottom bushing. Press the bottom bushing from the knuckle bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200514">Figure K>).</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
